rs make the acquisition of Rob Gronkowski official|website=bucsnation.com|last=Arcia|first=Gil||date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 New England Patriots Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n!Notes\n|-\n! [[List of New England Patriots first-round draft picks|1]] || 23\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | 3 || 87\n| <!--PLAYER--> || <!--POSITION--> || <!--COLLEGE-->\n|\n|-\n!98\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|[[National Football League Draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory pick]]\n|-\n!100\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|[[National Football League Draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory pick]]\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | 4 || 125\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Chicago Bears season|Chicago]]\n|-\n! 139\n| <!--PLAYER-->|| <!--POSITION-->|| <!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay]]<br>[[National Football League Draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory pick]]\n|-\n!5\n!172\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Seattle Seahawks season|Seattle]] via [[2020 Detroit Lions season|Detroit]]\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" | 6 || 195\n| <!--PLAYER-->|| <!--POSITION-->|| <!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Denver Broncos season|Denver]]\n|-\n! 204\n| <!--PLAYER-->|| <!--POSITION-->|| <!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Houston Texans season|Houston]]\n|-\n!212\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|[[National Football League Draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory pick]]\n|-\n!213\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|[[National Football League Draft#Compensatory picks|Compensatory pick]]\n|-\n! 7 || 230\n|<!--PLAYER-->\n|<!--POSITION-->\n|<!--COLLEGE-->\n|from [[2020 Atlanta Falcons season|Atlanta]]\n|}\n'''Notes'''\n* New England traded a second-round selection (No. 55 overall) to the [[Atlanta Falcons]] in exchange for wide receiver [[Mohamed Sanu]].\n* New England acquired a 2020 fourth-round selection (No. 125 overall) as part of a trade that sent their [[2019 NFL Draft|2019]] third- and sixth-round selections to the [[Chicago Bears]].\n*New England acquired a 2020 fourth-round selection (No. 139 overall) as part of a trade that sent [[tight end]] [[Rob Gronkowski]] and a seventh-round selection (No. 241 overall) to the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]].\n**New England acquired the seventh-round selection (No. 241 overall) as part of a trade that sent [[tight end]] [[Jacob Hollister]] to the [[Seattle Seahawks]]. \n*New England traded a fourth-round selection (No. 129 overall) to the [[Baltimore Ravens]] in exchange for offensive lineman [[Jermaine Eluemunor]] and a sixth-round selection (No. 207 overall).\n**New England later traded the sixth-round selection (No. 207 overall) to the [[Buffalo Bills]] in exchange for [[Center (gridiron football)|center]] [[Russell Bodine]].\n* New England traded a fifth-round selection (No. 168 overall) to the [[Philadelphia Eagles]] in exchange for a seventh-round selection (No. 235 overall) and defensive lineman [[Michael Bennett (defensive lineman, born 1985)|Michael Bennett]].\n**New England later acquired a fifth-round selection (No. 172 overall) as a part of a trade that sent [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Duron Harmon]] and the seventh-round selection (No. 235 overall) to the [[Detroit Lions]].\n* New England acquired a sixth-round selection (No. 195 overall) as part of a trade that sent [[cornerback]] [[Duke Dawson]] and a seventh-round selection (No. 237 overall) to the [[Denver Broncos]].\n*New England traded a sixth-round selection (No. 202 overall) to the [[Arizona Cardinals]] in exchange for [[Tackle (gridiron football position)|offensive tackle]] [[Korey Cunningham]].\n*New England acquired a sixth-round selection (No. 204 overall) as part of a trade that sent [[cornerback]] [[Keion Crossen]] to the [[Houston Texans]]. \n*New England acquired a seventh-round selection (No. 230 overall) as part of a trade that sent [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Jordan Richards (American football)|Jordan Richards]] to the [[Atlanta Falcons]].\n* As the result of the negative differential of free agent signings and departures that the Patriots experienced during the first wave of the [[2019 NFL season|2019]] free agency period, the team received the league-maximum four [[National Football League draft#Compensatory picks|compensatory selection]]s for the 2020 draft.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Compensatory Draft Picks Update (5/13/2019) |url=https://overthecap.com/2020-compensatory-draft-picks-update-5-13-2019/ |work=Over The Cap |date=May 13, 2019 |accessdate=May 13, 2019}}</ref> Free agent transactions that occurred after May 7, 2019 did not factor into the team's formula for determining compensatory selections.<ref>{{cite web |last=Teope |first=Herbie |title=Tuesday deadline marks next wave of free agency |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001030106/article/tuesday-deadline-marks-next-wave-of-free-agency |work=NFL |date=May 7, 2019 |accessdate=May 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Staff==\n{{New England Patriots staff}}\n\n==Current roster==\n{{New England Patriots roster}}\n\n==Preseason==\nThe Patriots' preseason opponents and schedule will be announced in the spring.\n\n==Regular season==\n<!--===Schedule===-->\n===2020 opponents===\nListed below are the Patriots' opponents for [[2020 NFL season|2020]]. Exact dates and times will be announced in the spring.<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Opponents Determined |url=https://nflcommunications.com/Pages/2020-Opponents-Determined.aspx |work=NFL Communications |date=December 30, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\"| Category 