ermon.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Quarterback|QB]]\n|[[Cody Kessler]]\n|\n|April 1, 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rostermon.com/teams/ne/transactions/|title=New England Patriots Transactions|website=rostermon.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Retirements ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Position\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Player\n! style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\" |Date retired\n|-\n|[[Tight end|TE]]\n|[[Benjamin Watson]]\n|March 18, 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rostermon.com/player/593/|title=Ben Watson|website=rostermon.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Trades ===\n\n* March 18: the Patriots traded [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Duron Harmon]] and a 2020 seventh-round selection (No. 235 overall) to the [[2020 Detroit Lions season|Detroit Lions]] in exchange for the Lions' 2020 fifth-round selection (No. 172 overall).<ref>{{Cite \nweb|url=http://rostermon.com/teams/ne/transactions/|title=New England Patriots Transactions|website=rostermon.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n* April 21: the Patriots traded [[tight end]] [[Rob Gronkowski]] and a 2020 seventh-round selection (No. 241 overall) to the [[2020 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] for the Buccaneers' fourth-round selection (No. 139 overall).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bucsnation.com/2020/4/21/21230551/buccaneers-rob-gronkowski-official-patriots|title=Buccaneers make the acquisition of Rob Gronkowski official|website=bucsnation.com|last=Arcia|first=Gil||date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n==Draft==\n{{main|2020 NFL Draft}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|New England Patriots|year=2020|border=2}}\"| 2020 New England Patriots Draft\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n!Notes\n|-\n! [[List of 